County: Rutherford County  State: North Carolina

*Galex aphylla* L.

Rhizomatous, acaulescent, glabrous herb. Leaves evergreen, ovate, dentate-serrate, base cordate. Flowers in a raceme, on a nonbracteate scape. Petals(5), white, separate, adnate to the staminal tube. Stamens united.

Shiloah, NC south on SR 1106 to Broad River, then downstream approx ¼ mile and up a small unnamed stream approx ¼ mile. Growing along the top bank of the stream.

Collected by: James E. Padgett Date: 5-17-01
